i can't always get to krispy kreme so someone help me homemade doughnuts how super easy doughnuts ingredients tablespoons white vinegar cup milk tablespoons shortening cup white sugar egg teaspoon vanilla extract cups sifted all purpose flour teaspoon baking soda teaspoon salt quart oil for deep frying cup confectioners' sugar for dusting directions stir the vinegar into the milk and let stand for a few minutes until thick in a medium bowl cream together the shortening and sugar until smooth beat in the egg and vanilla until well blended sift together the flour baking soda and salt stir into the sugar mixture alternating with the vinegar and milk roll dough out on a floured surface to inch thickness cut into doughnuts using a donut cutter let stand for about minutes heat the oil in a large deep skillet to degrees f degrees c fry doughnuts in the hot oil until golden turning over once drain on paper towels dust with confectioners' sugar while they are still warm and serve immediately Mayonnaise Bread Japanese cuisine Vinegar Doughnut Pancake Tofu Ice cream Soul food Jewish cuisine Halva Haggis Flour Rice pudding Puff pastry Tea Coffee German cuisine Chocolate Cuisine of the Philippines Tortilla Cuisine of Denmark Cookie Dim sum Cuisine of Singapore Cooking weights and measures Chili con carne Cheese Brewery Pizza Krispy Kreme French fries Fried dough foods Cuisine of Malaysia Polish cuisine Carbon dioxide Baked Alaska Dumpling Bagel Dairy Bengali cuisine Sushi Fish and chips Milkshake Turkish coffee Flax Chowder Ramen Barbecue Sugar In-N-Out Burger Milk Cake Hot dog Peruvian cuisine Mooncake Confectionery Soy milk Cuisine of the Southern United States D__ner kebab Cajun cuisine Muffin Wok Cuisine of Austria Toffee Volume Soy protein Idli Ketchup Custard Tapioca Cuisine of Brazil Cookware and bakeware Stir frying Plastic Kraft Dinner Kit Kat Dosa Curry Potato chips Scrambled eggs Hemp Paint McDonald's Soft drink Chocolate Salty Balls Soup Cantonese cuisine Cannabis cu